                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ms3kn1p/manifest/annotation/p1",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(center)\">\n                <addressee>Rev. Mr I. Leeser</addressee>\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Chicago</placeName>\n                <date>March 10<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1851</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>Dear Sir!</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Your esteemed favor of <date>18'</date> of last month is<lb/> before\n                me, in reply to which I would like to treat of business first<lb/> &amp; of\n                    <sic>miscellanious</sic> things afterwards. We are owing you incl. The<lb/> now\n                ending vol. of the Occident $11.00, of which we have to deduct an<lb/> outlay for\n                postage on the <date>23' March 1848</date> for books send to <persName>S.\n                    Coh.</persName> Here<lb/> $—73 remaining $10.72, for which please to find an\n                order to <placeName>N. Y.</placeName><lb/> enclosed, acknowledging its receipt in\n                the next Occident.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Your bill against <persName>S. Coh</persName> we have\n                presented,<lb/> to which he replied as follows: I have remitted <persName>Mr\n                    Leeser</persName> on the<lb/>\n                <date><hi rend=\"underline\">23' Jan 1848</hi></date> by you (respect.\n                    <persName>Kohn</persName>, the same having been send in the letter<lb/> ordering\n                the Occident) Three Dollars, then again I have receipt for<lb/> Three Dollars in the\n                Occident of <date><hi rend=\"underline\">June 1849</hi></date>, &amp; Six Dollars were\n                send<lb/> by me to <persName>Mr Leeser</persName> some time in <date>Febr.</date>\n                Last, which makes up the 12<lb/> Dollars, the amount of the bill. I hope it is in\n                order, please<lb/> to write about it.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">In regard to your retiring from your office<lb/> last fall, I felt\n                sorry when reading of it, there must have been<lb/> a serious misunderstanding\n                between you &amp; your congr. to have caused<lb/> such a step, as far as I could\n                learn, you acted the part of a<lb/> man of self respect by retiring. I regret very\n                much, that I<lb/> could not do much with your circulars, to procure you new\n                subscribers<lb/> there is too much <sic>indifferism</sic> amongst <add>יהודים</add>\n                about their holy Religion<lb/> its defenders, or any thing out of trade, it is\n                    <sic>realy</sic> deplorable, but<lb/> let us hope for better in the future. I\n                have always looked<lb/> upon the Occid. as a welcome visitor, I like its tendency\n                &amp; spirit<lb/> &amp; shall always peruse any of the volumes with pleasure &amp;\n                satisfaction.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">But <persName>Mr Leeser</persName> I would <sic>advice</sic> you one\n                thing<lb/> that if you do wish more subscribers for your Occ. or weekly<lb/> paper\n                about to be published, do come out on a Editors Tour<lb/> to the west, &amp; by\n                personally soliciting subscribers to your Periodicals</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ms3kn1p/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
