                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ms3kn1p/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"indent(1)\">you will get 10 subscribers, to one you might get without<lb/> it.\n                If you start after <add>פסח</add> &amp; go to <placeName>New York</placeName>\n                <placeName>Albany</placeName>\n                <placeName>Utica</placeName><lb/>\n                <placeName>Syracuse</placeName>\n                <placeName>Rochester</placeName>\n                <placeName><sic>Bufalo</sic></placeName>\n                <placeName>Erie</placeName>\n                <placeName>Cleveland</placeName>\n                <placeName>Sandusky</placeName>\n                <placeName>Toledo</placeName>\n                <placeName>Detroit</placeName><lb/>\n                <placeName>Milwaukee</placeName>\n                <placeName>Chicago</placeName>\n                <placeName>Peru</placeName>\n                <placeName>Pevria<add>?</add></placeName>\n                <placeName>St Louis</placeName>, &amp; then down the\n                <placeName>Miss.</placeName><lb/> &amp; <placeName>Ohio</placeName> up towards\n                    <placeName>Cincinatti</placeName> &amp; home again, I will warrant you<lb/> a\n                great many new names on your Lists, &amp; they pay all, which<lb/> is a principal\n                thing. From <placeName>Albany West</placeName> you will find<lb/>\n                <add>יהודים</add> in every town or City of little importance, who will take<lb/>\n                your Occ. if they see you &amp; the paper. There area great many<lb/> who never\n                heard of it, do come out &amp; show it to them, tell them<lb/> that it is a\n                necessary Book in their families, particularly for<lb/> those who live isolated in\n                places where there are only a few<lb/> &amp; no <add>קהלה</add> or Synagogue. Please\n                look on the maps and<lb/> note every little town from here down the\n                    <placeName>Illinois River</placeName> to <placeName>St Louis</placeName><lb/>\n                &amp; from there on the <placeName>Miss.</placeName> &amp; then to\n                    <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> &amp; you will find<lb/>\n                <add>יהודים</add> in every town of importance, who will take your paper<lb/> if you\n                present it yourself. The Exp. of <sic>travelling</sic> will come out<lb/> of it.\n                This is a friendly advice of mine, you may take it<lb/> into consideration, it is\n                given gratis, &amp; with the best intentions.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">They are at present forming a Congreg. at <placeName>Detroit<lb/>\n                    Mich</placeName>, another has been started at <placeName>Milwaukee</placeName>,\n                where there<lb/> are a great many families congregated from\n                    <placeName>Bohemia</placeName>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Here we began a <add>קהל</add> 3 years ago with 15 members<lb/> we\n                now number 40 paying members, have a Burial Ground, &amp; by<lb/> building a\n                Synagogue now, we are under an Expense of ca<lb/> 2200 Dollars to come out of the\n                pockets of the members. There<lb/> are a good many things besides building a\n                Synagogue to be wished<lb/> but patience &amp; perseverance will accomplish a great\n                many things.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">By and bye, the Asmonean lately had an article<lb/> from a Corresp.\n                from here, in which it states that by the liberality<lb/> of the\n                    <placeName>NY.</placeName> merchant we are enabled to go on with our work<lb/>\n                of building, this is not a fact, all we got from <placeName>NY.</placeName> Was<lb/>\n                from <hi rend=\"underline\">60 to 65 Dollars</hi>, honor to whom honor is due!</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ms3kn1p/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
